This section features the writing assignments required for this course. Each
assignment is due during the class session indicated below. (Note: Not all
class sessions have assignments.)
***** A Note on Critical Reflections *****
[Amazon_logo] These assignments are based on the text A World of Ideas,
abbreviated below as IDEAS (Jacobus, Lee A. A World of Ideas: Essential Reading
for College Writers. 7th ed. Boston, MA: Bedford/Saint Martin's, 2005. ISBN:
9780312437176.)
Students were required to turn in a total of three critical reflections only.
Only the first critical reflection was mandatory; the second and third ones
were turned in depending on which critical reflections each student chose. The
guidelines for the critical reflections are provided below in Ses #4 and apply
to all subsequent reflections.
